    "explanation": "Since 6y6995945x4 is divisible by 72, it must be divisible by 9\nand 8 (coprime factors of 72).\nIf last 3-digits of a number is divisible by 8, then the given\nnumber is also divisible by 8.\nHence, x = 0, 4, 8\nGiven that x=2y therefore possible values of y = 0, 2, 4\nAlso, Sum of digits must be divisible by 9\n6+y+6+9+9+5+9+4+5+x+4\n57+x+y\t⇒\nCase 1 : When x=0, y=0\n57+0+0 = 57 (not divisible by 9)\nCase 2: When x=4, y=2\n57+4+2 = 63 (completely divisible by 9)\nCase 3: When x=8, y=4\n57+8+4 = 69 (not divisible by 9)\nClearly the desired values of x and y are 4 and 2 respectively.\n\n\n-- \n= = 4\t√xy √42",
