    "correctIndex": 0,
    "explanation": "Possessive pronouns- They are the pronouns that\nhelp us show possession or ownership in a sentence.\nPossessive pronouns are mine, yours, his, hers, its, ours, yours,\nand theirs. They refer back to a noun or noun phrase already\nused, replacing it to avoid repetition: \"I said that the mistake\nwas mine.\"\nMy, your, his, her, its, our, your, and their. They function as\ndeterminers in front of a noun to describe who something\nbelongs to: \"I said that's my mistake.\".\nHence, ‘Our’ will be replaced by ‘ours’ to make the sentence\ngrammatically correct.\n\n\n\n\nSSC TIER-1 MOCK TEST",
