    "id": "q-ssc-cgl-test-ssc-cgl-full-3283-maths-1",
    "text": "6 boys from school A and 8 boys from school B together can set up an exhibition in 6 days, while 6 boys from school A and 12 boys from school C together can do in 5 days or 4 boys from school B and 6 boys from school C together can do in 10 days. Then how many boys from school A can set up the exhibition in one day? / विालय A के 6 लड़के तथा विालय B के 8 लड़के मिलकर 6 दिनों में एक दशनी का आयोजन करते हैं जबिक विालय A के 6 लड़के और विालय C के 12 लड़के मिलकर यह काय 5 दिनों में कर सकते हैं या विालय B के 4 लड़के तथा विालय C के 6 लड़के एक साथ इसे 10 दिनों में कर सकते हैं | विालय A के कितने लड़के इस दशनी का आयोजन एक दिन में कर सकते हैं ?",
    "options": [
      "48",
      "72",
      "60",
      "68"
    ],
    "correctIndex": 0,
    "explanation": "(6A+8B) 6=(6A + 12C) = (4B + 6C)\t× \t× 5 \t0\t× 1\n= using 2nd & 3rd case.\n= (6A + 12C) = (4B + 6C)\t× 5 \t0\t× 1\n30A + 60C = 40B + 60C\n=B\nA\n\n\nIt means efficiency of each boy of school A is 4 unit, efficiency\nof each boy of school B is 3 unit.\n6 boys from school A and 8 boys from school B together can set\nup an exhibition in 6 days,\nTotal work = (6 + 8 ) = 48\t× 4 × 3 × 6 \t× 6\nLet x boys can set up an exhibition of school A, efficiency of\neach student of A = 4 unit\n4x = 48 × 6\nx = 72",
    "sectionName": "Quantitative Aptitude",
    "testId": "test-ssc-cgl-full-3283"
